- unfreezeIfFrozen
- setBlockWrites
- openIndexIfClosed
- refresh
- deleteDestIfExists
- createIndex

To:

- removeMetadataBlocks
- openIndexIfClosed
- setReadOnly
- refresh
- deleteDestIfExists
- createIndex

In the older version (ref f2d591802c789cb0dcf6ff3ea7738d9b3d823d2a), the code still contains the checks for read and metadata blocks and the chain includes unfreezeIfFrozen and setBlockWrites but does not have removeMetadataBlocks or setReadOnly.

Also, the functions removeMetadataBlocks and setReadOnly do not exist in the older version, but unfreezeIfFrozen and setBlockWrites do.

Given this, the patch in the newer version introduces new logic and functions that do not exist in the older version, so the patch cannot be directly applied.

The best approach for backporting is to remove the block checks and replace the chain with the closest equivalent in the older version, adapting for the missing functions.

Specifically:

- Remove these lines:
  ```
  if (settingsBefore.getAsBoolean(IndexMetadata.SETTING_BLOCKS_READ, false)) {
      var errorMessage = String.format(Locale.ROOT, "Cannot reindex index [%s] which has a read block.", destIndexName);
      listener.onFailure(new ElasticsearchException(errorMessage));
      return;
  }
  if (settingsBefore.getAsBoolean(IndexMetadata.SETTING_BLOCKS_METADATA, false)) {
      var errorMessage = String.format(Locale.ROOT, "Cannot reindex index [%s] which has a metadata block.", destIndexName);
      listener.onFailure(new ElasticsearchException(errorMessage));
      return;
  }
  ```

- Change the chain from:
  ```
  SubscribableListener.<FreezeResponse>newForked(l -> unfreezeIfFrozen(sourceIndexName, sourceIndex, l, taskId))
      .<AcknowledgedResponse>andThen(l -> setBlockWrites(sourceIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<OpenIndexResponse>andThen(l -> openIndexIfClosed(sourceIndexName, wasClosed, l, taskId))
      .<BroadcastResponse>andThen(l -> refresh(sourceIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<AcknowledgedResponse>andThen(l -> deleteDestIfExists(destIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<AcknowledgedResponse>andThen(l -> createIndex(sourceIndex, destIndexName, l, taskId))
  ```

To:

  ```
  SubscribableListener.<AcknowledgedResponse>newForked(l -> setBlockWrites(sourceIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<OpenIndexResponse>andThen(l -> openIndexIfClosed(sourceIndexName, wasClosed, l, taskId))
      .<BroadcastResponse>andThen(l -> refresh(sourceIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<AcknowledgedResponse>andThen(l -> deleteDestIfExists(destIndexName, l, taskId))
      .<AcknowledgedResponse>andThen(l -> createIndex(sourceIndex, destIndexName, l, taskId))
  ```

This is the closest equivalent logic in the older version, removing the block checks and the unfreezeIfFrozen call, as the newer patch does.

